section.section:
Before a risk retention group offers insurance in this State, the risk retention group shall submit to the Commissioner:
a statement that identifies:
the state or states in which the risk retention group is chartered and licensed as a liability insurance company;
the date of chartering and licensing;
the principal place of business of the risk retention group; and
any other information, including information on membership of the risk retention group, that the Commissioner requires to verify that the risk retention group qualifies as a risk retention group, as defined in § 25-101 of this subtitle;
subject to paragraphs (2) and (3) of this subsection, a copy of the plan of operation or feasibility study of the risk retention group and any revisions of the plan of operation or feasibility study submitted to the state in which the risk retention group is chartered and licensed;
a statement of registration that designates the Commissioner as its agent for service of legal process;
a copy of the financial statement of the risk retention group that:
was submitted to the state in which the risk retention group is chartered and licensed;
is certified by an independent certified public accountant; and
contains a statement of opinion on loss and loss adjustment expense reserves made by a member of the American Academy of Actuaries or a qualified loss reserve specialist;
a copy of each examination of the risk retention group that is certified by the Commissioner or other public official that conducts the examination;
on request of the Commissioner, a copy of any information or document that relates to an outside audit performed with respect to the risk retention group; and
any other information that the Commissioner requires in order to verify the continuing qualification of the risk retention group as a risk retention group, as defined in § 25-101 of this subtitle.
